collections.name: Axolopepe
collections.description:
Axolopepe is an art collection that expresses the critical situation of the Axolotl species.

The axolotl is a Mexican amphibian that is characterized by its ability to regenerate lost limbs and stay “young” throughout its life. This phenomenon is called neoteny.

The axolotl is critically endangered. Its habitat has been reduced to the canals of Xochimilco and its population is decreasing every year. The main causes of its decline are pollution, the introduction of fish species that compete with or prey on the axolotl, overexploitation and capture for food, and the pet trade.

A percentage of the proceeds will be used to help rehabilitate axolotl habitat, conserve local wildlife, and strengthen agricultural practices.

This program is not affiliated with any political party. Its use for purposes other than those established is prohibited.

collections.name: Ancient Sun
collections.description:
On a sweltering summer day, I found myself sitting in the shade of Persepolis’ majestic columns, waiting for the sun to soften its fiery intensity, for the perfect moment to arrive. Hours slipped by as the sunlight gracefully danced between the ancient columns, casting long shadows across the stones. It was then that inspiration struck—this light, this ethereal glow, could become a vital element in my composition. I waited, patiently, for the sun to dip closer to the horizon, painting the sky with hues of gold and crimson. Meticulously, I adjusted the color temperature of my camera—what photographers call Kelvin—pushing it higher to amplify the fiery reds of the sunset.

I took several practice shots, each one fine-tuning the balance of light and composition, until the moment I had envisioned came to life. I captured it—a frame filled with history, warmth, and light. As I prepared to move on, something stopped me. A lone figure appeared in the distance, slowly stepping into the scene. I waited, watching as he walked with a calm, deliberate pace. And then, just as he reached the perfect spot, I clicked the shutter.

a man seemingly emerging from a gateway to eternity, walking toward a path that vanished into the horizon. The towering columns, steadfast and unyielding, stood witness. The sun, a timeless companion of this land, cast its glow with unwavering warmth. And history itself—etched into every stone—stood alive, radiant, and eternal.

This image is more than just a photograph. It is a testament to the countless lives that have traversed this soil, each leaving behind a trace, each contributing to the legacy of this ancient land. The light and the warmth that cradle this history remain unyielding, symbols of resilience and grandeur. It is the enduring essence of the lion and the sun—a timeless emblem of this land’s soul.
